Iaas and paas :

* Running application on data centre is called 
Iass ( infrastructure as a service)
* We will install the virtual machine, os, software and then manually deploy the application in there.
* Use only infrastructure from cloud provider.
Ex: using vm service to deploy your apps/databases Ec2 
*  Cloud provider is responsible for: 
      Hardware, networking & virtualization 
 •. You are responsible for those 

Paas ( platform as service )
When you are using platform as service you are making use of platform provide by the cloud 
Ex: AWS elastic beanstalk 
Just go there and run your application 
Scaling, hardware, networking, os, application runtime, load balancing.
• You are responsible for configuration of application and services
Application code if needed 
Platform as a database are amazon RDS 

Containers & Orchestration : 

Microservices enterprises are heading towards 
*Build small focused microservices 
• Flexibility to innovate and build applications in different programming languages ( Go, java, python, etc ) 
• but deployment becomes complex.
• how can we have one way of deployment in micro 
   enter containers
 • Containers - Docker 
 • create docker images for each microservice 
 • docker images has all needs of a microservice 
    • Application code and dependencies 
    • runs the same way on any infrastructure 
          * your local machine 
          *  Corporate data centre
          *   Cloud 
   • Advantages 
      • Docker container are light weight 
         • Compared to vm as they do not have a                 guest os
         * Docker provides isolation for containers 
         * Docker is cloud neutral.
         
Container orchestration: 
• Requirement I want 10 instances of microservice a container, 15 instances of microservice B container and soon..
• Typical features :
    • Auto scaling - scale containers based on demand 
    • service discovery - Help microservices find one another 
    • Load balance - Distribute load among multiple instances of a microservice 
    • self Healing - Do health checks and replace failing instances 
    • zero downtime deployments - Relase new versions without downtime.

Container orchestration services:
Using a container orchestration: 
 1: create a cluster 
